 \int^L_{-L}{\frac{1}{(z^2+x^2)^{\frac{3}{2}}}}dx 
x = z\cdot tan\theta
z^2 + x^2 = z^2\cdot sec^2\theta
dx = z\cdot sec^2\theta d\theta
x = L \to tan\theta = \dfrac{L}{z} \to \theta = tan^{-1}(\frac{L}{z})
I = 2\dot \displaystyle \int_{0}^{tan^{-1}(\frac{L}{z})} \dfrac{1}{z^2}\cdot cos\theta d\theta = \dfrac{2\cdot sin\left(tan^{-1}(\frac{L}{z})\right)}{z^2} = \dfrac{2L}{z^2\sqrt{z^2 + L^2}}
